          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1702404335148-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>with the <strong>remaining ground</strong> <strong>coriander</strong>, <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>garam</strong> <strong>masala</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>green</strong> <strong>chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>cardamom</strong> <strong>seeds</strong></p><p>Cook for 1-2 min further or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1702404344551-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1702404344551-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1702404344551-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1702404344551-x1000.jpg",
