          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1702404350829-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>basmati</strong> <strong>rice </strong>with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>cardamom</strong> <strong>pods</strong>, the <strong>bay</strong> <strong>leaf[ves]</strong>, a pinch of<strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>salt</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving – this is your<strong> fragrant rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1702404357766-x200.jpg",
